# Force LF in the working tree on every platform. A few tests in
# hostess/testdata compare fixture files byte-for-byte against output the code
# builds with \n (TestFormatLinux / TestFormatWindows in
# hostess/hostlist_test.go). Without this git's autocrlf default rewrites those
# fixtures to CRLF when CI checks them out on Windows, so the comparison fails
# even though the visible text is identical. text=auto still lets git detect
# binaries so they are left alone.
* text=auto eol=lf
